Define a method named createAcronym that takes a string parameter and returns the acronym of the string 
parameter. Append a period (.) after each letter in the acronym. If a word begins with a lower case letter,
don't include that letter in the acronym. Then write a main program that reads a phrase from input, calls
createAcronym() with the input phrase as argument, and outputs the returned acronym. Assume the input has at
least one upper case letter.
     If the input is:                            the output should be:
    Association for computing MACHINERY            A.M

import java.util.Scanner;

public class LabProgram {
   public static String createAcronym(String userPhrase){
      String acronym = "";
      String[] words = userPhrase.split(" ");   // split phrase into words
      for (String word : words) {
         if (!word.isEmpty() && Character.isUpperCase(word.charAt(0))) {
            acronym += word.charAt(0) + "."; // append uppercase first letter + period
         }
      }

      return acronym;
   }
   
   public static void main(String[] args) {
      Scanner scnr = new Scanner (System.in);
      String userPhrase = scnr.nextLine();
      
      String acronym = createAcronym(userPhrase);
      System.out.println(acronym);
      
   }
}


